==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prattle
<hw>Prat"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Prattled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Prattling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Freq.
<ets>of prate</ets>.]</ety> <def>To talk much and idly; to prate; hence,
to talk lightly and artlessly, like a child; to utter child's
talk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prattle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prattle
<hw>Prat"tle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To utter as prattle; to babble;
<as>as, to <ex>prattle</ex> treason</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prattle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prattle
<hw>Prat"tle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Trifling or childish tattle; empty
talk; loquacity on trivial subjects; prate; babble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mere <qex>prattle</qex>, without practice.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prattlement</ent>⟦br⟧
